<br />

<div class="separator" style="text-align: center;">
<a href="https://media.licdn.com/mpr/mpr/AAEAAQAAAAAAAAO4AAAAJDFkMjA5OWI3LTE3MmUtNGIyMC1iZTVkLTNjZDc1ODYzM2I1NA.jpg" style="color: #b4445c; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="books, books, books" border="0" height="267" src="https://cdn.finotto.org/uploads/2015/10/27022226/read-more-cover-1100x733.jpg" title="Source: Michele Finotto" width="400" />
</a></div>

<br />

<div style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial, tahoma, helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">
<b>"What we really need is not more authors,
</b>
</span>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial, tahoma, helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">
<b>or better publishers.&nbsp;
</b>
</span>
<b style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">What we most need is&nbsp;
</b>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial, tahoma, helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">
<b>a vastly better system to identify the books we will love."
</b>
</span>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial, tahoma, helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">
<br />
</div>

<div style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial, tahoma, helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: center;">
<span style="color: #7d181e; font-family: arial; font-size: large;">
<a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/01/16/book-it-baby/" style="color: #7d181e; text-decoration-line: none;" target="_blank">TechCrunch</a>
<br />
<br />
</span>
</div>

<span face="" style="background-color: white; color: #111111;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Beantown Web has developed such a system.&nbsp; For the ninth year running Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published during the calendar year. These books are most likely to add value to your career.
</span>

<br />
<br />

<span style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial; font-size: large;">This year's search began by identifying 11 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. Presented here are the results.
</span>

<br />
<br />

</span>

<div style="background-color: white;">
<span style="color: #111111; font-family: arial; font-size: large;">A total of 110 books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list -- 77 of these books were mentioned only once.
</span>

<br />
<br />

<h3 style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: x-large;">The Honorable Mention Shelf</span>
</h3>

<br />

<span style="color: #111111; font-family: arial; font-size: large;">
An additional 15 books were mentioned on two lists and these books comprise the <b>Honorable Mention</b> list.
</span>

